# DubbiOvi

AI-Assisted Audiovisual Translation Environment

Developed within Alfonso Digital Lab
Department of English, French and German Philology
University of Oviedo

## Overview

DubbiOvi is an open-source web application designed for audiovisual translation, dubbing adaptation, teaching, and research.

The platform integrates:

* Video playback
* Script segmentation
* AI-assisted translation suggestions
* Terminology management
* Import and export workflows
* Real-time project synchronization

## Current Features

* Video import
* Script import (.docx, .txt, .json)
* Segment management
* AI-assisted translation with Gemini
* Glossary support
* Firebase synchronization

## Planned Features

* Automatic speech recognition (ASR)
* Automatic video transcription
* Speaker detection
* Timeline enhancement
* Lip-sync assistance
* Research analytics

## Intended Use

DubbiOvi has been developed for:

* Audiovisual Translation teaching
* Translation Technology courses
* Machine Translation Post-Editing training
* Translation Studies research
* Knowledge transfer activities

